main event: On August 30, 1954 in Minneapolis, Minnesota, a civilian reported observing five white or silver circle-shaped objects with no trail or sound, moving in a circular formation at an elevation of 60 degrees and azimuth of 75 degrees before disappearing. The observation lasted 3-4 minutes.
